>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Where should I practice defense and dodge?</span><hr size=1> I finally got my grubby hands on the dodge skill, but my defense is still lagging a bit, only around 66 when it's currently capped at 81 for level 22.  I need to find blues that hit quickly but not hard so I can max those skills, since it will only get more painful as I get higher in levels.  Anyone know where I can find monsters gentle to my frail, anemic caster body? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ujochangaladar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jochan Galadar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 570<br> <font color=#333333>(9/10/02 7:16:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=351.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Where should I practice defense and dodge?</span><hr size=1>     It shouldn't be too difficult to max your defense skills just by ds'ing yourself and hunting any blues you find.  Use the &quot;caster tank&quot; approach with ds, shock of flame, and your pet beating from behind. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ualucard101.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alucard101</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 43<br> <font color=#333333>(9/10/02 7:23:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=351.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   where..? </span><hr size=1> shouldn't it be when? <br>
since mage can't really heal himself well after taken damage.... but with item inflations... it doesn't hurt as much as it should at lower lvls.<br>
<br>
Also... If you do want to tank.. i think u can try old zones like ... LGuk <br>
or OOT... (not OOT if you are 60. til 53ish maybe?)<br>
<br>
seafuries only hits for 70ish.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ueuphorion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Euphorion</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 163<br> <font color=#333333>(9/10/02 7:29:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=351.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: where..? </span><hr size=1> Go to echo Caverns and hunt Needlites beginning at lvl 24.<br>
Go take some hits when you are unhurt and let your &quot;phantom spell&quot; heal you. (or bandage to 50% always if you like some risk).<br>
They hit VERY fast, but for VERY little damage.<br>
<br>
You could stay there (in that part of echo caverns) until lvl 31 (from 29 on you will not only kill the Needlites per 18-minutes-respawn-cycle, but also some Boglings and Mutants) and by this you should be able to get your defense close to the very maximum.<br>
<br>
I can't tell how sad I am that I didn't recognize defense as important earlier and didn't use the chance Echo Caverns offered me...<br>
Now I need to let MOBs hit me that hardly hit under 100 and it is VERY VERY painful to get any defense increases... <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=170427" target="_blank">
<img src="http://www.euphorion.org/sig/euph_zdd2.jpg" border="0">
</a> 
