Hollyniu 35 Monk
Member of Tears of Doom</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uelliot70.showPublicProfile?language=EN>elliot70</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(9/10/02 11:18:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=351.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: where..? </span><hr size=1> One thing you can try is to get 2 65hp, 6ac rings, ask a high level friend to come along and group with her or him.<br>
<br>
If they are high enough then you won't get any exp and level at all until you have your skills up to a point where you want to start regaining exp. Just get a decent slasher or blunt weapon, send your pet in and start tanking.<br>
<br>
Personally I think the best partner would be a high level shaman. they can buff you right up with 49th level spells like Harnessing, stamina etc. etc. and you should be able to tank for a long time without any problems. Also, if you find a shaman friend then they can also regen/chloro you so you won't have a problem getting your hit points back.<br>
<br>
For a mage defence isn't THAT important since the skill stops at 145 but every point of defence gives you that little extra comfort zone so getting it up should always be a priority.<br>
<br>
